      <item>
        <title>Whonix XFCE 14.0.0.9.6 for VirtualBox released!</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[Patrick]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>barbara:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>A stupid question: will those last changes be reflected with sudo apt-get update &amp;&amp; sudo apt-get dist-upgrade or is it required to download and import the .ova files again?</p>
</blockquote>
<p>That’s actually a complex question to answer.</p>
<p>Everything that is very important: Will be reflected by usual upgrades.<br>
Otherwise a separate Whonix news will be posted.</p>
<p>Everything that is not crucial (usability improvements): This includes<br>
changes to everything configured in user’s home folder. Everything that<br>
Whonix has to ship in /etc/skel due to technical limitations. Such as<br>
the change from xfce standard start menu to whiskermenu will not be done<br>
automatically by upgrades. This - if you want this (not important for<br>
anonymity/privacy/security) - you have to do that manually.</p>
          <p><a href="http://forums.whonix.org/t/whonix-xfce-14-0-0-9-6-for-virtualbox-released/6368/31">Read full topic</a></p>
